From: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>
Date: Tue, 09 Jun 2026 11:26:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] crypto/hmac: reject keys shorter than 128 bits in fips mode
References: jsc#PED-15986,bsc#1266284
Patch-mainline: Not yet, downstream provision to maintain cert validity beyond 2030.

Currently, the minimum key length accepted in fips mode by the hmac
implementation is 112 bits. However, keys shorter than 128 bits will
be disallowed by 2030. Increase the minimum from 112 to 128 bits.

Signed-off-by: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>
---
 crypto/hmac.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/crypto/hmac.c
+++ b/crypto/hmac.c
@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@ static int hmac_setkey(struct crypto_sha
 	SHASH_DESC_ON_STACK(shash, hash);
 	unsigned int i;
 
-	if (fips_enabled && (keylen < 112 / 8))
+	if (fips_enabled && (keylen < 128 / 8))
 		return -EINVAL;
 
 	shash->tfm = hash;
